Main article: COVID-19 pandemic in Nepal

The table below documents the daily growth and change of laboratory-confirmed COVID-19 cases, deaths, and recoveries and RT-PCR tests in Nepal, since the country's first confirmed case on 23 January 2020. The figures for confirmed cases, recoveries, and deaths until 8 June have been largely derived from Worldometer's archived pages and cross-checked with its Nepal coronavirus page, while those for RT-PCR tests have had to be mostly obtained from the Ministry of Health and Population (MoHP)'s COVID-19 situation reports. Some numbers for cases, recoveries, and deaths found in the MoHP's situation reports (e.g., #103, #102, etc.) until 8 June conflict with the ones derived from Worldometer. In such cases, Worldometer's numbers have been used, given the website's tendency to quickly incorporate new updates.
